        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "TO...",
        "bbox": [
          0.8183556413624247,
          0.7441860467613225,
          0.8451242828249562,
          0.7529069764218169
        ],
        "order": 31
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2023.12.09_page_009_6",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "said it would take an impairment charge of around £25bn ($31.5bn), as it writes down the carry value of its cigarette assets over the next 3o years. The company, which counts Dunhill, Kent and Lucky Strike among its brands, aims to get half its revenue from smokeless products by 2035.",
        "bbox": [
          0.061185467666082016,
          0.7848837210517464,
          0.2619502874894061,
          0.9156976743162601
        ],
        "order": 33
      },
      {
